1
00:00:08,833 --> 00:00:10,833
[machinery whirring]

2
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:15,875
[Kuga] Mibu!

3
00:00:16,583 --> 00:00:17,416
Look.

4
00:00:18,708 --> 00:00:19,708
[Mibu] Hm?

5
00:00:19,791 --> 00:00:22,625
Someone left flowers
in the same spot again.

6
00:00:23,166 --> 00:00:24,083
Oh.

7
00:00:24,666 --> 00:00:26,125
It's just an old grudge.

8
00:00:26,958 --> 00:00:28,041
Don't worry about it.

9
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:30,625
Okay.

10
00:00:30,708 --> 00:00:31,916
[tense music playing]

11
00:00:32,541 --> 00:00:34,250
[Kyogoku sighs]

12
00:00:34,333 --> 00:00:37,416
The smell of freshly-laundered sheets.

13
00:00:38,791 --> 00:00:40,625
Thanks to you, President Koyama,

14
00:00:40,708 --> 00:00:43,833
I get to enjoy all the comforts
of a luxury hotel.

15
00:00:43,916 --> 00:00:45,000
You're a big help.

16
00:00:45,583 --> 00:00:47,583
I owe you big time, Mr. Kyogoku.

17
00:00:48,250 --> 00:00:51,208
It's no trouble at all
to book a room for you in my name.

18
00:00:51,291 --> 00:00:52,666
It's the least I can do.

19
00:00:54,541 --> 00:00:56,541
[ice cubes clinking]

20
00:01:02,791 --> 00:01:05,125
People in our world
don't get to stay in hotels

21
00:01:05,208 --> 00:01:08,041
where they need your ID to check you in.

22
00:01:08,833 --> 00:01:11,791
We use a fake name, we do time for fraud.

23
00:01:11,875 --> 00:01:13,208
Even with all our money,

24
00:01:13,291 --> 00:01:16,416
we're forced to stay
in crummy love hotels.

25
00:01:19,291 --> 00:01:22,958
[groans] I took care of that thing
you asked me to do.

26
00:01:23,041 --> 00:01:23,875
Huh?

27
00:01:23,958 --> 00:01:25,916
The thing with the idiot stepfather.

28
00:01:26,500 --> 00:01:31,375
<i>He ruined a top-earning girl,</i>
<i>Shizuku Pien, for a lousy three million.</i>

29
00:01:31,958 --> 00:01:33,958
<i>I couldn't let that stand.</i>

30
00:01:34,041 --> 00:01:36,083
<i>The stepfather sued us, so</i>

31
00:01:37,375 --> 00:01:40,125
<i>I fried his crotch</i>
<i>and turned him into a eunuch.</i>

32
00:01:40,625 --> 00:01:41,500
[groans]

33
00:01:41,583 --> 00:01:43,000
I saw a photo of the damage.

34
00:01:43,083 --> 00:01:46,000
[groans] He'll never use that thing again.

35
00:01:46,083 --> 00:01:47,500
[chuckles]

36
00:01:47,583 --> 00:01:52,541
For the rest of his life,
he'll need a catheter to take a leak.

37
00:01:53,541 --> 00:01:54,916
What, he's still alive?

38
00:01:57,875 --> 00:01:58,750
- [music ends]
- Eh?

39
00:01:58,833 --> 00:02:01,750
He could talk. You're sure about this?

40
00:02:02,458 --> 00:02:05,041
[ice cubes clinking]

41
00:02:08,583 --> 00:02:10,166
[sighs] What?

42
00:02:11,041 --> 00:02:12,166
You saying I should kill him?

43
00:02:13,791 --> 00:02:14,625
No. I, uh…

44
00:02:16,041 --> 00:02:17,416
[ice cubes clink]

45
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:18,916
[tense music resumes]

46
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:21,166
I'm saying that I need a refill.

47
00:02:22,083 --> 00:02:23,416
Are you deaf?

48
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:25,500
Uh, uh…

49
00:02:25,583 --> 00:02:27,125
I'm sorry. Right away.

50
00:02:27,208 --> 00:02:29,250
[fast-paced tense music playing]

51
00:02:35,458 --> 00:02:36,541
[Kyogoku sighs]

52
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,708
Don't worry about him squealing.

53
00:02:43,000 --> 00:02:45,708
Whatever he says,
they'll never connect it to you.

54
00:02:46,208 --> 00:02:48,625
Of course. Here you are, sir.

55
00:02:50,333 --> 00:02:53,583
[Kyogoku] Oh yeah, there's something else.
I need a favor from you.

56
00:02:53,666 --> 00:02:56,750
I want to borrow one of your best girls
for a day.

57
00:02:56,833 --> 00:02:59,750
Yes, sir. I'll arrange to have
our most popular actress sent right away.

58
00:02:59,833 --> 00:03:01,708
- Not that.
- Oh.

59
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:05,375
I want a homemade tape of a cocky CEO,
married with kids,

60
00:03:05,458 --> 00:03:07,750
getting it on with a porn star.

61
00:03:07,833 --> 00:03:10,000
We'll film them on the sly
and blackmail him.

62
00:03:10,083 --> 00:03:13,083
The long-term goal is
to take over his company.

63
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:15,083
To make it happen,
it'll take a little help

64
00:03:15,166 --> 00:03:16,250
from Attorney Kujo.

65
00:03:16,333 --> 00:03:17,833
He'll be our messenger.

66
00:03:23,875 --> 00:03:26,416
The bigger they are, the harder they fall.

67
00:03:29,458 --> 00:03:31,916
I'm gonna make him fall so hard.

68
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:34,500
[dramatic sting]

69
00:03:36,583 --> 00:03:37,666
[music fades]

70
00:03:37,750 --> 00:03:39,291
[Karasuma sighs]

71
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:42,666
Mr. Karasuma, what's the matter?
Are you feeling unwell?

72
00:03:42,750 --> 00:03:44,833
It's not exactly my body.
It's more like my soul.

73
00:03:44,916 --> 00:03:46,083
Your soul?

74
00:03:47,375 --> 00:03:49,375
When we deal with Mr. Mibu,
it leads to someone else.

75
00:03:51,083 --> 00:03:52,291
Who's the someone else?

76
00:03:52,375 --> 00:03:54,458
[sighs] As if you don't know.

77
00:03:55,583 --> 00:03:56,875
- Kyogoku--
- [door opens]

78
00:04:05,583 --> 00:04:07,791
Thank you for coming, Attorney Kujo.

79
00:04:08,583 --> 00:04:10,041
Do you remember?

80
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:13,208
I met you two before at Kiko,
the old folks' home.

81
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:14,416
Of course.

82
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:18,083
At the time, I wasn't aware
that Mr. Mibu and you were acquainted.

83
00:04:18,166 --> 00:04:22,041
I was there on Mr. Mibu's orders,
keeping on eye on President Sugawara.

84
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:26,041
[Sugawara] <i>Sharing this cup</i>
<i>makes us brothers.</i>

85
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:28,000
You turn on me, and I'll kill you.

86
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:32,000
I was caught
and beaten half to death. [chuckles]

87
00:04:32,083 --> 00:04:35,291
After all that,
I'm surprised you still work for Mr. Mibu.

88
00:04:36,375 --> 00:04:38,416
He saved my life. I owe him one.

89
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:42,625
Mr. Kuga.

90
00:04:43,125 --> 00:04:45,291
You've been arrested
on suspicion of contravening

91
00:04:45,375 --> 00:04:46,833
the Employment Security Act.

92
00:04:47,416 --> 00:04:50,083
They're claiming you recruited girls
to a call girl agency

93
00:04:50,166 --> 00:04:52,500
to get them involved in prostitution.

94
00:04:52,583 --> 00:04:53,750
[Kuga] Sir.

95
00:04:54,416 --> 00:04:55,958
I've been arrested on other charges.

96
00:04:56,041 --> 00:04:56,958
[upbeat music playing]

97
00:04:57,541 --> 00:04:59,875
What gives you the idea that
it's a separate arrest?

98
00:05:00,541 --> 00:05:03,166
A guy called Tonohata
works for the call girl agency.

99
00:05:03,250 --> 00:05:04,916
He drives the girls around.

100
00:05:05,000 --> 00:05:07,416
Someone snatched him
and messed him up last week.

101
00:05:07,958 --> 00:05:10,791
I was interrogated.
I'm considered a suspect, apparently.

102
00:05:10,875 --> 00:05:13,000
Do you have any idea why
they would think that?

103
00:05:13,833 --> 00:05:17,208
Tonohata's a jerk.
He set fire to my car a while ago.

104
00:05:17,708 --> 00:05:20,291
He was caught on a security camera,
so they arrested him right away.

105
00:05:20,375 --> 00:05:23,375
I guess the cops really leaned on him
to give them something.

106
00:05:24,750 --> 00:05:27,875
Sir, are they gonna put me away?

107
00:05:28,875 --> 00:05:31,416
Until I know exactly what
Mr. Tonohata has told the police,

108
00:05:31,500 --> 00:05:33,375
I can't give you a definitive answer.

109
00:05:35,416 --> 00:05:37,375
Were you involved in the assault
on Tonohata?

110
00:05:37,458 --> 00:05:39,083
No. It wasn't me

111
00:05:39,625 --> 00:05:42,250
I was in Fukuoka
the day that that went down.

112
00:05:43,125 --> 00:05:44,625
I understand. Fine.

113
00:05:45,125 --> 00:05:48,166
If that's all they've got for evidence,
say as little as possible.

114
00:05:48,250 --> 00:05:49,875
Clam up and you'll be okay.

115
00:05:51,291 --> 00:05:53,625
[Kuga] Clamming up might not be so easy.

116
00:05:53,708 --> 00:05:55,583
The detective in charge is annoying.

117
00:05:55,666 --> 00:05:58,416
This guy called Arashiyama
from the Organized Crime Division.

118
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,708
Arashiyama interrogated you?

119
00:05:59,791 --> 00:06:00,708
[Kuga] Yeah.

120
00:06:00,791 --> 00:06:04,500
The guy's got it in for me.
Always pushing my buttons. I don't know.

121
00:06:04,583 --> 00:06:06,125
I could easily mouth off to him.

122
00:06:06,208 --> 00:06:08,666
Do you have any idea why
he treats you so harshly?

123
00:06:11,833 --> 00:06:13,416
Arashiyama had a daughter.

124
00:06:15,083 --> 00:06:16,625
- [music ends]
- She was murdered.

125
00:06:16,708 --> 00:06:17,625
[music resumes]

126
00:06:17,708 --> 00:06:20,333
Prisoners, halt!

127
00:06:21,541 --> 00:06:22,875
Fall out!

128
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,083
[Kuga] <i>The one who killed her…</i>

129
00:06:27,166 --> 00:06:29,291
[guard] Left face. Lift them.

130
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:31,583
<i>…was a guy named Yuto Inukai.</i>

131
00:06:32,125 --> 00:06:33,541
<i>He was a friend of mine.</i>

132
00:06:33,625 --> 00:06:34,875
<i>We're from the same town.</i>

133
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:45,625
<i>That's why Arashiyama resents us.</i>

134
00:06:46,416 --> 00:06:48,833
<i>He's got it in for us. Me and Mibu.</i>

135
00:06:51,083 --> 00:06:52,000
[music fades]

136
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:53,791
[Kujo] Mr. Karasuma.

137
00:06:53,916 --> 00:06:55,250
HONJO POLICE STATION
STAFF ENTRANCE

138
00:06:55,333 --> 00:06:58,083
That shop with the sign that says
Japan's number one takoyaki…

139
00:06:58,166 --> 00:06:59,583
- Have you ever tried it?
- Huh?

140
00:06:59,666 --> 00:07:00,708
[Kujo] The takoyaki.

141
00:07:00,791 --> 00:07:03,250
[Karasuma] Now's not the time
to be thinking about food.

142
00:07:03,333 --> 00:07:04,958
Can't you take anything seriously?

143
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:07,000
Let's buy some today and see if it's true.

144
00:07:07,083 --> 00:07:08,666
We'll order extra mayonnaise, huh?

145
00:07:08,750 --> 00:07:10,333
[Arashiyama] Attorney Kujo.

146
00:07:11,875 --> 00:07:14,916
How does a lawyer like you become
the errand boy for thugs and Yakuza?

147
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:15,833
They paying you?

148
00:07:17,041 --> 00:07:19,875
You should watch what you say.
I could sue you.

149
00:07:19,958 --> 00:07:21,041
Let's see.

150
00:07:21,125 --> 00:07:24,833
So your father is the famous prosecutor,
Yukisada Kurama.

151
00:07:24,916 --> 00:07:28,250
You've got a big brother,
Kuroudo Kurama, also a prosecutor.

152
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:32,458
I hear your brother's got a big career
ahead of him, so keep out of his way.

153
00:07:33,958 --> 00:07:35,458
I wouldn't worry about that.

154
00:07:36,208 --> 00:07:38,666
We're individuals.
There's a world of difference between us.

155
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,500
You really shouldn't lump people together.

156
00:07:41,916 --> 00:07:44,208
Anyway,
I've already cut ties with my family.

157
00:07:44,291 --> 00:07:46,208
[Arashiyama] That's not what people say
about you.

158
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:50,416
Do you think I'm bothered
about what people say?

159
00:07:50,958 --> 00:07:52,291
If you'll excuse me.

160
00:07:53,083 --> 00:07:55,416
- [car engine starts]
- You're Attorney Karasuma, right?

161
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:56,791
That's right.

162
00:07:56,875 --> 00:08:00,208
You too, you're all about the cash?
But you're just a kid.

163
00:08:00,291 --> 00:08:02,625
Did you go to law school
to run errands for thugs?

164
00:08:02,708 --> 00:08:03,750
No, of course not.

165
00:08:07,250 --> 00:08:09,250
[melancholy music playing]

166
00:08:21,541 --> 00:08:23,541
[theme music playing]

167
00:08:56,500 --> 00:09:00,375
Is it true you cut ties with your brother
Prosecutor Kurama?

168
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:02,875
Yeah. It's true.

169
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:05,500
[Karasuma] Why did you do that?

170
00:09:18,208 --> 00:09:20,083
So… who were we just talking to?

171
00:09:23,416 --> 00:09:25,625
Detective Arashiyama from Organized Crime.

172
00:09:25,708 --> 00:09:27,875
Oh, that's the guy.

173
00:09:28,833 --> 00:09:30,750
I don't like how cops like him think.

174
00:09:31,791 --> 00:09:34,208
Detectives see the world in binary terms.

175
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:38,041
If you don't cooperate with them,
you're automatically a suspect.

176
00:09:38,125 --> 00:09:40,541
It's impossible to have
any real dialogue with them.

177
00:09:40,625 --> 00:09:43,666
So he's the detective
whose daughter was killed, right?

178
00:09:44,791 --> 00:09:47,541
Do you know anything about that case,
Mr. Kujo?

179
00:09:52,208 --> 00:09:53,708
It happened ten years ago.

180
00:09:53,791 --> 00:09:55,416
[inquisitive music playing]

181
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:58,291
[Kujo] <i>A woman's body was discovered</i>
<i>down by the river.</i>

182
00:10:01,125 --> 00:10:04,000
<i>The deceased was identified as</i>
<i>Manami Ogawa, 20 years old.</i>

183
00:10:04,500 --> 00:10:06,041
<i>She was Detective Arashiyama's daughter,</i>

184
00:10:06,125 --> 00:10:08,958
<i>but she went by her mother's last name</i>
<i>after the parents divorced.</i>

185
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:12,833
<i>Body fluids found at the scene indicated</i>
<i>there were multiple perpetrators.</i>

186
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:15,500
<i>And the police arrested several minors</i>
<i>in short order.</i>

187
00:10:15,583 --> 00:10:17,000
- [cop 1] Got anything?
- [cop 2] This.

188
00:10:17,083 --> 00:10:19,416
[Kujo] Manami Ogawa was attacked
from behind on her way home.

189
00:10:19,500 --> 00:10:21,375
The assailants took her money
and valuables.

190
00:10:21,458 --> 00:10:22,916
Then they raped her.

191
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,125
At some point, she started screaming,
so they strangled her to death.

192
00:10:28,250 --> 00:10:29,875
- [inmate 1] Second dish.
- [inmate 2] Third.

193
00:10:29,958 --> 00:10:31,666
- [inmate 3] First dish.
- [inmate 2] Third.

194
00:10:31,750 --> 00:10:34,333
[Kujo] <i>The one who did the killing</i>
<i>was Yuto Inukai.</i>

195
00:10:34,416 --> 00:10:36,458
<i>He was sentenced to between</i>
<i>ten and fifteen years,</i>

196
00:10:36,541 --> 00:10:39,333
<i>and he's still serving his time</i>
<i>in a juvenile facility.</i>

197
00:10:39,416 --> 00:10:42,041
<i>His two accomplices have already served</i>
<i>their sentences</i>

198
00:10:42,125 --> 00:10:43,958
<i>and are in rehabilitation programs.</i>

199
00:10:47,541 --> 00:10:50,583
[man] Detective Arashiyama,
are you sure Kuga's guilty?

200
00:10:50,666 --> 00:10:52,083
He's guilty as hell.

201
00:10:52,166 --> 00:10:55,375
[man] But he has an alibi for the day
of the incident. He was in Fukuoka. And--

202
00:10:55,458 --> 00:10:58,625
Fukami, unless you're paying
very close attention,

203
00:10:58,708 --> 00:11:02,750
a person's true nature
will be invisible to you.

204
00:11:02,833 --> 00:11:04,541
[Fukami] A person's true nature?

205
00:11:04,625 --> 00:11:08,000
People show the public one face.
They show the family another face.

206
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:09,333
Those aren't real.

207
00:11:10,208 --> 00:11:12,291
They show their true face
only to themselves

208
00:11:12,375 --> 00:11:14,125
and to those who share in their sins.

209
00:11:16,791 --> 00:11:18,041
Don't just look at the perp.

210
00:11:18,125 --> 00:11:21,208
Look at the victim too,
who they were, the world they were in.

211
00:11:21,291 --> 00:11:23,833
How did the crime come into
their lives and why?

212
00:11:23,916 --> 00:11:26,125
That's what every good investigation does.

213
00:11:27,416 --> 00:11:28,250
Sir.

214
00:11:28,333 --> 00:11:30,250
[Arashiyama] Okay, good job today.

215
00:11:30,333 --> 00:11:31,750
You're leaving?

216
00:11:31,833 --> 00:11:33,625
I have something to do at home.

217
00:11:35,750 --> 00:11:38,041
[Karasuma] Okay.
I get the basic picture of the case.

218
00:11:38,541 --> 00:11:41,000
Why does Detective Arashiyama
hate Mr. Mibu

219
00:11:41,083 --> 00:11:43,333
just because of an old connection
with Inukai?

220
00:11:44,416 --> 00:11:47,166
[Kujo] Hard to know for sure,
but if I had to guess,

221
00:11:47,250 --> 00:11:51,916
Detective Arashiyama knows that
Mr. Mibu is operating under Mr. Kyogoku.

222
00:11:54,041 --> 00:11:55,500
See, it's just what I was saying.

223
00:11:55,583 --> 00:11:58,250
Not a good idea
for us to work with Mr. Kyogoku.

224
00:11:59,291 --> 00:12:00,916
Now we're talking about
two of your clients

225
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,708
who could be implicated
in a murder, right?

226
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:06,625
If you get involved with people like that,
they'll disbar you for real.

227
00:12:06,708 --> 00:12:09,791
As I explained to you previously,
it's really just a guess.

228
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:17,916
So… are you saying
that the murder of Arashiyama's daughter

229
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,125
is still an open case?

230
00:12:20,750 --> 00:12:21,875
[music fades]

231
00:12:22,583 --> 00:12:24,000
[man] Hey, how'd it go?

232
00:12:24,625 --> 00:12:25,708
[Fukami] Uh…

233
00:12:26,541 --> 00:12:28,250
Where's Arashiyama, anyway?

234
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,458
He said he had something to do.

235
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,041
Keep a close eye on him.

236
00:12:33,166 --> 00:12:35,666
I'm getting worried about him, Fukami.

237
00:12:35,750 --> 00:12:36,583
Why?

238
00:12:39,250 --> 00:12:42,125
Pretty soon, they're releasing the guy.

239
00:13:01,875 --> 00:13:04,666
[Fukami] <i>Why is Arashiyama continuing</i>
<i>his own investigation</i>

240
00:13:04,750 --> 00:13:07,125
<i>even though the perpetrators</i>
<i>have been arrested?</i>

241
00:13:08,083 --> 00:13:09,750
[man] <i>He says it doesn't add up.</i>

242
00:13:10,541 --> 00:13:12,000
What doesn't add up?

243
00:13:13,625 --> 00:13:14,541
Come here.

244
00:13:17,916 --> 00:13:18,750
[man sighs]

245
00:13:20,583 --> 00:13:24,000
There's nothing to link the territory
where Inukai and his crew operated

246
00:13:24,083 --> 00:13:27,166
and the neighborhood
where Arashiyama's daughter lived.

247
00:13:28,166 --> 00:13:30,291
She wasn't even close to downtown.

248
00:13:30,375 --> 00:13:32,291
So why would they go out of their way
to be there?

249
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:34,125
In their statements,

250
00:13:34,208 --> 00:13:37,291
Inukai and the other two said
they didn't even know his daughter.

251
00:13:37,375 --> 00:13:41,708
So he suspects
that someone ordered them to do it.

252
00:13:42,583 --> 00:13:44,458
Maybe it was Mibu.

253
00:13:44,541 --> 00:13:47,041
Or the guys above him,
the Fushimi-gumi gang.

254
00:13:47,125 --> 00:13:48,375
[jazzy music playing]

255
00:13:48,458 --> 00:13:51,333
Yeah, but talk about not adding up.
Why would that be?

256
00:13:52,875 --> 00:13:54,875
[man] <i>He says he's playing a hunch.</i>

257
00:13:55,375 --> 00:13:56,708
[Fukami] <i>But the trial is over.</i>

258
00:13:56,791 --> 00:14:00,166
<i>The perpetrators were convicted,</i>
<i>and the sentences were finalized.</i>

259
00:14:00,250 --> 00:14:01,416
<i>Isn't it all too late?</i>

260
00:14:01,500 --> 00:14:05,208
<i>And isn't Arashiyama investigating</i>
<i>by himself, as a private citizen?</i>

261
00:14:10,833 --> 00:14:14,500
[man] <i>They found her cell phone</i>
<i>among her belongings, but it was locked.</i>

262
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,875
<i>Nowadays,</i>
<i>you can get a tech expert to unlock it</i>

263
00:14:17,958 --> 00:14:19,750
<i>for about 500,000.</i>

264
00:14:20,666 --> 00:14:23,000
<i>Back in those days, it wasn't possible.</i>

265
00:14:23,958 --> 00:14:27,833
<i>The investigation is complete,</i>
<i>the case is closed, the trial is over,</i>

266
00:14:27,916 --> 00:14:30,291
<i>but nothing's over for Arashiyama.</i>

267
00:14:33,541 --> 00:14:37,125
<i>A six-digit passcode has</i>
<i>a million possible combinations.</i>

268
00:14:37,208 --> 00:14:39,333
Enter the wrong code too many times,

269
00:14:39,416 --> 00:14:41,000
<i>the phone locks you out for a day.</i>

270
00:14:41,083 --> 00:14:44,125
<i>He's been at it for years,</i>
<i>day after day in limbo.</i>

271
00:14:45,708 --> 00:14:48,875
<i>The probability of unlocking that phone</i>
<i>is one in a million.</i>

272
00:14:49,458 --> 00:14:51,875
[Fukami] <i>Why doesn't he just pay</i>
<i>a professional?</i>

273
00:14:54,250 --> 00:14:56,125
[man] It's a father's obsession.

274
00:14:57,125 --> 00:14:59,000
<i>Compulsively trying to unlock her phone</i>

275
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:02,208
<i>is the only way he can feel connected</i>
<i>to his murdered daughter.</i>

276
00:15:06,666 --> 00:15:07,833
[music stops]

277
00:15:15,833 --> 00:15:18,291
[inhales deeply, exhales]

278
00:15:19,125 --> 00:15:20,625
It's a miracle.

279
00:15:20,708 --> 00:15:21,833
[exhales shakily]

280
00:15:22,958 --> 00:15:25,916
On the anniversary of her death,
a miracle.

281
00:15:26,833 --> 00:15:28,125
[inhales]

282
00:15:29,375 --> 00:15:31,375
[exhales shakily]

283
00:15:38,291 --> 00:15:40,625
HISTORY

284
00:15:43,375 --> 00:15:46,250
MIHO

285
00:15:48,041 --> 00:15:51,166
MIHO, MANAMI

286
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:52,375
[sniffs]

287
00:15:53,916 --> 00:15:55,500
MIHO
CALLING…

288
00:15:55,583 --> 00:15:56,625
[line ringing]

289
00:16:02,375 --> 00:16:03,250
[line clicks]

290
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:05,708
[gasps]

291
00:16:06,500 --> 00:16:08,958
- [woman] <i>Uh… Hello?</i>
- [clears throat]

292
00:16:10,375 --> 00:16:12,375
Uh… [sniffs]

293
00:16:12,958 --> 00:16:15,458
This is the father of Manami Ogawa.

294
00:16:16,125 --> 00:16:18,125
[breathing shakily]

295
00:16:19,583 --> 00:16:22,291
[woman] <i>Manami's… father?</i>

296
00:16:23,916 --> 00:16:24,875
[grunts]

297
00:16:24,958 --> 00:16:26,333
Would it be okay

298
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:30,500
for me to ask you something
about my daughter?

299
00:16:32,541 --> 00:16:34,541
[baby crying]

300
00:16:49,583 --> 00:16:50,666
[Arashiyama] Uh.

301
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:55,333
Hello, there.
You're Ms. Miho Kinugasa, right?

302
00:16:55,416 --> 00:16:57,541
I'm Arashiyama. We spoke on the phone.

303
00:16:58,333 --> 00:16:59,166
Oh.

304
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:01,250
Hi. Nice to meet you.

305
00:17:02,625 --> 00:17:05,208
- Uh…
- [baby continues crying]

306
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:07,791
How did you know my daughter,
Ms. Kinugasa?

307
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:12,291
You could call us drinking buddies,
I guess.

308
00:17:15,166 --> 00:17:17,416
Manami,
she wasn't really a drinker, was she?

309
00:17:18,000 --> 00:17:19,500
Sure, she drank.

310
00:17:19,583 --> 00:17:21,750
I'd say… quite a lot.

311
00:17:22,750 --> 00:17:25,958
We were, like, the early adopters
of the paid drinking thing.

312
00:17:26,958 --> 00:17:32,583
In Nishiazabu, usually, or Roppongi,
we'd meet up and do a bit of drinking.

313
00:17:32,666 --> 00:17:33,791
What's paid drinking?

314
00:17:33,875 --> 00:17:36,458
- With CEOs in, like, IT.
- [somber music playing]

315
00:17:36,541 --> 00:17:39,541
Rich guys, you know.
who like to party with girls around.

316
00:17:39,625 --> 00:17:42,291
We usually didn't know
what they did for a living.

317
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:46,375
We'd hang out and drink with them
and get 30,000 for the evening.

318
00:17:46,458 --> 00:17:48,708
Thirty thousand?
All that for just drinking?

319
00:17:48,791 --> 00:17:52,666
[chuckles] Yeah.
And now I'm a 30-something single mom.

320
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:55,500
I guess I won't be getting
that kind of gig again.

321
00:17:57,416 --> 00:18:00,250
The baby's crying.
Shouldn't you do something about that?

322
00:18:00,333 --> 00:18:03,208
Oh. He'll be fine.

323
00:18:03,291 --> 00:18:06,541
If I don't let him cry in the day,
he really goes for it at night.

324
00:18:07,125 --> 00:18:08,291
And before I know it,

325
00:18:08,375 --> 00:18:10,916
I've got the guy next door
banging on the wall.

326
00:18:12,916 --> 00:18:14,916
[baby cries intensely]

327
00:18:17,333 --> 00:18:19,875
Um… Ms. Kinugasa,

328
00:18:20,500 --> 00:18:23,250
can you give me the contact information
for those executives,

329
00:18:23,333 --> 00:18:24,416
the men you drank with?

330
00:18:24,500 --> 00:18:27,750
Uh… I don't have a clue how to reach them.

331
00:18:30,208 --> 00:18:32,250
There I was,
constantly obsessed with work,

332
00:18:32,333 --> 00:18:35,000
and I barely knew anything
about my own daughter.

333
00:18:37,250 --> 00:18:40,541
That was before.
Now, I want to know everything.

334
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,791
Is there anything you can remember
that might help me?

335
00:18:50,208 --> 00:18:51,708
Let's see if it's still there.

336
00:18:52,708 --> 00:18:54,583
Manami's alt account.

337
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:56,833
Alt account?

338
00:18:56,916 --> 00:18:58,583
Mm. Like social media.

339
00:18:59,208 --> 00:19:00,083
Uh…

340
00:19:01,708 --> 00:19:02,625
Here it is.

341
00:19:02,708 --> 00:19:03,541
IMPOSSIBLE CAT

342
00:19:03,625 --> 00:19:04,916
[music fades]

343
00:19:09,583 --> 00:19:12,166
Thank you very much for your cooperation.

344
00:19:16,166 --> 00:19:17,000
You know…

345
00:19:19,541 --> 00:19:21,875
I'm struggling to make ends meet
right now.

346
00:19:23,083 --> 00:19:25,583
I went out of my way
and made time to talk to you,

347
00:19:25,666 --> 00:19:27,875
so how about you give me 30,000 yen?

348
00:19:31,708 --> 00:19:34,250
So you weren't cooperating
because you cared?

349
00:19:34,333 --> 00:19:36,250
You were just looking to score some cash?

350
00:19:37,458 --> 00:19:40,166
That comes from having made money
the easy way.

351
00:19:41,333 --> 00:19:43,791
How do you hope to raise a child
with such an attitude?

352
00:19:43,875 --> 00:19:45,458
[baby continues crying]

353
00:19:46,333 --> 00:19:49,500
Screw you.
You're just like she said you were.

354
00:19:50,958 --> 00:19:53,208
You know, old man, your daughter hated you

355
00:19:53,291 --> 00:19:56,083
because of that self-important way
you look down on everyone.

356
00:20:07,333 --> 00:20:08,500
I SAW KOYASHAN’S PHONE.

357
00:20:08,583 --> 00:20:11,291
THERE WERE PICTURES OF HIS WIFE AND BABY.
I WAS BEING DECEIVED.

358
00:20:12,416 --> 00:20:14,125
[Manami] <i>I want to be praised.</i>

359
00:20:15,250 --> 00:20:17,500
<i>Even if it's a lie,</i>
<i>I just want to be praised.</i>

360
00:20:18,916 --> 00:20:20,916
Were you that needy, Manami?

361
00:20:23,125 --> 00:20:24,750
[Manami] <i>I saw Koyashan's phone.</i>

362
00:20:26,291 --> 00:20:30,208
<i>There were pictures of his beautiful wife</i>
<i>and newborn baby.</i>

363
00:20:31,250 --> 00:20:32,750
<i>I was being deceived.</i>

364
00:20:33,958 --> 00:20:35,375
An affair?

365
00:20:36,583 --> 00:20:41,083
[Manami] <i>At one point, Koyashan was</i>
<i>the father of a child of mine, you know?</i>

366
00:20:41,166 --> 00:20:42,166
[exhales sharply]

367
00:20:42,250 --> 00:20:44,250
[mournful choral music playing]

368
00:20:47,541 --> 00:20:50,875
[Manami] <i>Dad's job is to punish bad people</i>
<i>for what they did wrong.</i>

369
00:20:52,458 --> 00:20:56,291
<i>He would say, "If anything bad</i>
<i>happens to you, tell Dad."</i>

370
00:20:57,875 --> 00:21:02,083
<i>But Dad was constantly working late,</i>
<i>and we hardly ever got a chance to talk.</i>

371
00:21:03,458 --> 00:21:07,625
<i>Bad things were happening all the time</i>
<i>in my life, but I couldn't say anything.</i>

372
00:21:09,708 --> 00:21:12,666
<i>I'm going to tell Koyashan's wife</i>
<i>about our relationship.</i>

373
00:21:13,208 --> 00:21:15,916
<i>I'm going to tell my dad</i>
<i>all of his secrets.</i>

374
00:21:16,416 --> 00:21:19,250
<i>If I have to live in hell,</i>
<i>Koyashan's coming with me.</i>

375
00:21:22,125 --> 00:21:24,958
<i>I finally plucked up the courage</i>
<i>to call Dad.</i>

376
00:21:26,083 --> 00:21:28,125
<i>I wanted to ask his advice.</i>

377
00:21:29,583 --> 00:21:31,666
<i>What should I do</i>
<i>with my jealousy and anger?</i>

378
00:21:31,750 --> 00:21:33,458
<i>Is it okay to give way to them?</i>

379
00:21:33,958 --> 00:21:37,916
<i>I'm worried that I'll do something wrong.</i>
<i>I don't wanna lose my way.</i>

380
00:21:39,416 --> 00:21:41,000
<i>What would Dad have said to guide me?</i>

381
00:21:41,083 --> 00:21:42,291
DAD
CALLING…

382
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:43,541
MANAMI

383
00:21:43,625 --> 00:21:44,666
[phone ringing]

384
00:21:50,958 --> 00:21:52,500
Is there a problem, Arashiyama?

385
00:21:52,583 --> 00:21:53,666
No, no. It's all good.

386
00:21:53,750 --> 00:21:55,250
- Let's go.
- [cops] Yes, sir.

387
00:21:55,333 --> 00:21:56,333
[man] Okay, then.

388
00:21:57,500 --> 00:21:59,791
[Arashiyama] <i>I was way too busy with work.</i>

389
00:22:01,500 --> 00:22:03,083
<i>So, I ignored the call.</i>

390
00:22:03,875 --> 00:22:05,458
BUT I COULDN’T TELL HIM.

391
00:22:05,541 --> 00:22:07,541
[mournful choral music playing]

392
00:22:14,375 --> 00:22:16,375
[sobbing]

393
00:22:38,916 --> 00:22:40,000
[music ends]

394
00:22:45,958 --> 00:22:46,958
[Koyama sighs]

395
00:22:48,041 --> 00:22:50,375
President Koyama, what is this place?

396
00:22:50,458 --> 00:22:51,583
Oh, uh…

397
00:22:52,250 --> 00:22:54,458
Just an empty room
that was used for hookups.

398
00:22:54,541 --> 00:22:56,208
You're welcome to use it anytime.

399
00:22:56,291 --> 00:22:58,916
Consider it a favor from Mr. Kyogoku.

400
00:22:59,958 --> 00:23:02,500
MR. KYOGOKU
CALLING…

401
00:23:05,625 --> 00:23:08,916
<i>Ah, Mr. Kujo, it's Kyogoku.</i>

402
00:23:09,458 --> 00:23:10,416
[slurps]

403
00:23:11,291 --> 00:23:12,416
[grunts]

404
00:23:12,500 --> 00:23:15,583
The room you're in now…
It's yours. Whenever you want it.

405
00:23:16,166 --> 00:23:17,583
Where's this coming from?

406
00:23:18,208 --> 00:23:20,583
[Kyogoku] <i>Mibu told me</i>
<i>you're camped out on the roof.</i>

407
00:23:20,666 --> 00:23:23,666
<i>I'm worried that</i>
<i>you'll get sick living that way.</i>

408
00:23:24,541 --> 00:23:26,083
No, thanks, Mr. Kyogoku.

409
00:23:26,583 --> 00:23:29,250
I would much rather find a house
on my own terms.

410
00:23:29,333 --> 00:23:31,333
[grunts] Mmm.

411
00:23:32,791 --> 00:23:35,041
Well, then, Attorney…

412
00:23:36,875 --> 00:23:39,083
How about you go on retainer
with President Koyama?

413
00:23:39,166 --> 00:23:40,458
[tense music playing]

414
00:23:40,541 --> 00:23:42,833
[Kyogoku] <i>The president</i>
<i>will pay you plenty.</i>

415
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:45,708
<i>I can really use a guy with your skills.</i>

416
00:23:46,291 --> 00:23:48,458
I've got a long list of companies
that need advising.

417
00:23:48,541 --> 00:23:52,541
Well, it's true they're all,
uh, a little on the shady side.

418
00:23:52,625 --> 00:23:56,291
I never say not to a client on the basis
of social status or moral judgment.

419
00:23:56,375 --> 00:23:58,083
However,
I won't work on retainer for anyone.

420
00:24:00,250 --> 00:24:01,458
What the hell's the difference?

421
00:24:11,250 --> 00:24:12,916
Well, whatever.

422
00:24:13,916 --> 00:24:15,416
If you don't like the carrot,

423
00:24:16,041 --> 00:24:18,458
I'm just gonna have to hit you
with the stick.

424
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:22,291
Soon enough, Attorney Kujo.

425
00:24:23,125 --> 00:24:27,750
<i>I'm gonna make you</i>
<i>my obedient little carrier pigeon.</i>

426
00:24:28,666 --> 00:24:30,666
[music builds]

427
00:24:35,208 --> 00:24:37,208
[music fades]

428
00:24:39,791 --> 00:24:41,791
[ratcheting]

429
00:24:46,500 --> 00:24:47,583
Mr. Mibu.

430
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:49,500
Mr. Karasuma.

431
00:24:50,625 --> 00:24:52,000
Where's Mr. Kujo?

432
00:24:52,083 --> 00:24:52,958
Uh…

433
00:24:53,041 --> 00:24:54,208
[Mibu] You came alone?

434
00:24:54,291 --> 00:24:55,208
Yeah.

435
00:24:55,291 --> 00:24:56,416
[Mibu scoffs]

436
00:24:56,500 --> 00:24:58,000
Well, that's a first.

437
00:24:58,083 --> 00:24:59,333
So, what's up?

438
00:24:59,916 --> 00:25:02,666
Mr. Mibu,
have you met Detective Arashiyama?

439
00:25:02,750 --> 00:25:04,708
From the Organized Crime Division.

440
00:25:05,541 --> 00:25:06,416
Maybe.

441
00:25:07,291 --> 00:25:09,458
What's he like as a detective?

442
00:25:11,708 --> 00:25:13,291
The kind of cop who's always bugging you.

443
00:25:13,375 --> 00:25:15,750
The kind that treats guys like me
worse than animals.

444
00:25:16,541 --> 00:25:18,666
He hauls your ass in
for the stupidest thing

445
00:25:18,750 --> 00:25:21,916
and bullshit half the time,
and his interrogations are ruthless.

446
00:25:22,500 --> 00:25:25,541
I suppose that's the right thing
for a detective to do, isn't it?

447
00:25:26,083 --> 00:25:28,458
Is that the right thing
for an attorney to say?

448
00:25:32,666 --> 00:25:34,250
Were you just about done here?

449
00:25:35,791 --> 00:25:39,041
I'd like you to talk to me about
Detective Arashiyama's daughter.

450
00:25:39,125 --> 00:25:40,333
About her murder case.

451
00:25:43,208 --> 00:25:45,541
You're starting to sound like a detective.

452
00:25:46,041 --> 00:25:48,666
No, I'm not trying to find out
exactly what happened,

453
00:25:49,541 --> 00:25:53,375
just whether Mr. Kyogoku or you
were involved in the case somehow.

454
00:25:53,458 --> 00:25:54,666
Yeah, we were.

455
00:25:58,041 --> 00:25:59,625
What if I said that?

456
00:26:01,791 --> 00:26:04,125
Cut all your ties to Attorney Kujo
right away then, please.

457
00:26:04,208 --> 00:26:06,208
[upbeat music playing]

458
00:26:11,625 --> 00:26:14,000
Detective Arashiyama will stop at nothing

459
00:26:14,083 --> 00:26:16,208
to get to the bottom
of his daughter's murder.

460
00:26:16,291 --> 00:26:19,708
I wouldn't put it past him to make up
a reason to arrest Attorney Kujo.

461
00:26:20,500 --> 00:26:22,875
If any charges stuck
and he were found guilty,

462
00:26:23,541 --> 00:26:26,875
he'd be disbarred for life,
and we'd both be finished.

463
00:26:26,958 --> 00:26:29,916
That's not gonna happen.
I need Attorney Kujo too.

464
00:26:31,083 --> 00:26:32,833
I'll protect him no matter what.

465
00:26:40,708 --> 00:26:42,166
So step away from him right now.

466
00:26:45,333 --> 00:26:47,041
You'll give Attorney Kujo your protection

467
00:26:47,125 --> 00:26:49,333
just so you can use him
for your own advantage.

468
00:26:49,416 --> 00:26:50,666
It's about money for you.

469
00:26:53,458 --> 00:26:54,875
But I'm not like you.

470
00:26:56,916 --> 00:27:00,500
Attorney Kujo is the only lawyer I know
who defends the weak and those in need.

471
00:27:02,458 --> 00:27:03,833
I wanna protect that.

472
00:27:05,041 --> 00:27:07,958
So, if we don't have him,
who's gonna protect us?

473
00:27:17,416 --> 00:27:18,833
There's always you.

474
00:27:20,208 --> 00:27:22,125
You should be the next Attorney Kujo.

475
00:27:23,041 --> 00:27:24,208
Become that kind of lawyer.

476
00:27:28,625 --> 00:27:32,958
Anyway,
isn't it up to Attorney Kujo himself

477
00:27:33,041 --> 00:27:35,416
to choose if he wants
to stay away from us?

478
00:27:40,708 --> 00:27:42,708
[music fades]

479
00:28:06,125 --> 00:28:08,333
ORGANIZED CRIME DIVISION

480
00:28:08,416 --> 00:28:10,208
[Fukami] Uh, wait here
for a moment, please.

481
00:28:15,958 --> 00:28:17,083
Detective Arashiyama.

482
00:28:17,166 --> 00:28:18,041
Yeah?

483
00:28:18,125 --> 00:28:19,750
There's a woman who wants to talk to you.

484
00:28:26,250 --> 00:28:28,791
All right. Do you remember something?

485
00:28:29,750 --> 00:28:33,541
I'm sorry, Ms. Kinugasa.
I'm afraid there's nothing I can pay you.

486
00:28:35,458 --> 00:28:36,958
Your kid's quiet today.

487
00:28:38,208 --> 00:28:40,083
I thought about it, and I realized.

488
00:28:41,083 --> 00:28:42,458
Manami was the only one.

489
00:28:44,041 --> 00:28:46,833
Nobody else gave a damn. [chuckles]

490
00:28:46,916 --> 00:28:48,958
Manami was the only one
who really listened

491
00:28:49,041 --> 00:28:50,666
when I was going through things.

492
00:28:52,166 --> 00:28:53,250
You know,

493
00:28:54,125 --> 00:28:57,708
everyone was, like, worried about
getting dragged down with me.

494
00:28:58,208 --> 00:29:01,083
Social relationships
are such a hassle, huh?

495
00:29:02,666 --> 00:29:05,208
Sometimes, I think if Manami were alive,

496
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,791
we could've ended up being good friends.

497
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:14,250
Okay, so what do you remember?

498
00:29:15,416 --> 00:29:16,750
That guy, Koyashan,

499
00:29:18,333 --> 00:29:23,333
he was… you know… a pimp or whatever.

500
00:29:23,416 --> 00:29:24,625
[tense music playing]

501
00:29:24,708 --> 00:29:26,583
And that worked how?

502
00:29:26,666 --> 00:29:31,166
He'd get to know struggling pop singers
or swimsuit models

503
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:34,041
and introduce them to rich guys
as escorts,

504
00:29:34,125 --> 00:29:35,416
and he'd get a percentage.

505
00:29:43,250 --> 00:29:45,250
He was going out with Manami at the time.

506
00:29:47,916 --> 00:29:49,416
His name's Yoshiaki Koyama.

507
00:29:49,500 --> 00:29:52,250
[music increases in tempo]

508
00:29:56,958 --> 00:29:59,583
- Hey. I was talking to Fukami.
- Huh?

509
00:30:00,208 --> 00:30:03,125
He told me you've been looking
into your daughter's case.

510
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:07,083
While I'm totally sympathetic,

511
00:30:07,166 --> 00:30:09,500
we solved that case ten years ago.

512
00:30:09,583 --> 00:30:11,958
How about working on
what's in front of you, huh?

513
00:30:16,500 --> 00:30:17,500
[music fades]

514
00:30:19,166 --> 00:30:21,833
With all due respect, Lieutenant Sumiyama,

515
00:30:21,916 --> 00:30:23,833
I'm convinced nothing's been solved.

516
00:30:24,958 --> 00:30:26,708
If we can't act on our convictions,

517
00:30:26,791 --> 00:30:29,000
how can we be asked
to put our lives on the line?

518
00:30:29,541 --> 00:30:32,791
We risk our lives
because we believe in justice.

519
00:30:32,875 --> 00:30:34,125
[music resumes]

520
00:30:34,208 --> 00:30:35,791
Listen, Arashiyama.

521
00:30:35,875 --> 00:30:39,208
The system decides
what we mean by justice.

522
00:30:39,291 --> 00:30:42,125
You wanna run the system?
Improve your arrest rates.

523
00:30:43,291 --> 00:30:45,958
Forget about investigating
a 10-year-old case, okay?

524
00:30:47,083 --> 00:30:48,541
If you think that's unfair,

525
00:30:49,083 --> 00:30:52,000
whine all you want on your own time,
but suck it up at work.

526
00:30:52,083 --> 00:30:54,375
Hey. Arashiyama.

527
00:30:54,458 --> 00:30:55,541
[music fades]

528
00:30:55,625 --> 00:30:59,000
Just like Mr. Kujo said.
20 days and they cut you loose.

529
00:30:59,083 --> 00:30:59,958
Yeah.

530
00:31:00,041 --> 00:31:02,833
Hey, Mr. Mibu,
you set me up with a great attorney.

531
00:31:02,916 --> 00:31:04,375
Much appreciated.

532
00:31:04,458 --> 00:31:05,625
Was clamming up hard?

533
00:31:05,708 --> 00:31:07,000
I'll say.

534
00:31:07,083 --> 00:31:08,625
Arashiyama sank his damn teeth in.

535
00:31:09,291 --> 00:31:10,666
Arashiyama, huh?

536
00:31:11,833 --> 00:31:12,875
Oh.

537
00:31:12,958 --> 00:31:15,333
Inukai. He'll be getting out soon, right?

538
00:31:17,208 --> 00:31:18,041
Yeah.

539
00:31:24,125 --> 00:31:26,125
[dramatic music playing]

540
00:31:27,666 --> 00:31:29,833
[woman] Attorney Kujo, please!

541
00:31:29,916 --> 00:31:32,250
I can't forgive my ex-husband!

542
00:31:32,333 --> 00:31:34,333
[crying hysterically]

543
00:31:34,416 --> 00:31:36,125
[Yakushimae] Sachiko, please calm down.

544
00:31:36,208 --> 00:31:37,916
[Kujo] Start by telling me the details?

545
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,000
[Sachiko] I can't forgive him!

546
00:31:42,541 --> 00:31:44,000
[Sachiko sobs]

547
00:31:56,375 --> 00:31:58,291
Ms. Kinugasa, this is Arashiyama.

548
00:31:59,583 --> 00:32:01,083
Is now a good time to talk?

549
00:32:01,166 --> 00:32:04,500
Yeah, sure.
If you don't mind keeping it short.

550
00:32:06,708 --> 00:32:11,833
In Manami's messages,
I keep seeing P5 and P7.

551
00:32:11,916 --> 00:32:12,833
What do they mean?

552
00:32:12,916 --> 00:32:16,208
[Miho] Oh.
Those are the rates for prostitution.

553
00:32:16,291 --> 00:32:19,666
It means 50,000 and 70,000 yen
for sugar dating.

554
00:32:20,625 --> 00:32:23,750
<i>Two hours for one means paid drinking.</i>

555
00:32:25,541 --> 00:32:29,333
I didn't want to go into the details
because the truth is, well…

556
00:32:29,416 --> 00:32:31,166
<i>Koyashan's a little scary.</i>

557
00:32:31,250 --> 00:32:34,875
<i>But now that I'm a parent myself,</i>
<i>I think I get how you must feel,</i>

558
00:32:34,958 --> 00:32:36,541
<i>so I'll tell you some stuff.</i>

559
00:32:37,833 --> 00:32:38,791
Go on.

560
00:32:39,291 --> 00:32:42,000
The guy had plenty of young girlfriends.

561
00:32:42,083 --> 00:32:44,208
He made them do PCP,

562
00:32:44,291 --> 00:32:46,666
<i>got them really scared of the Yakuza,</i>

563
00:32:46,750 --> 00:32:48,958
<i>and forced them into sex work.</i>

564
00:32:50,833 --> 00:32:53,250
<i>Girls who always fight with their dads,</i>
<i>you know,</i>

565
00:32:53,833 --> 00:32:56,250
<i>the ones who never got praise</i>
<i>from their parents.</i>

566
00:32:56,750 --> 00:33:00,958
<i>They grow up feeling totally worthless,</i>
<i>so they never develop any self-confidence.</i>

567
00:33:01,916 --> 00:33:04,291
They turn to romantic relationships
for validation,

568
00:33:04,375 --> 00:33:07,625
even if it means always submitting
to the other person's demands.

569
00:33:08,458 --> 00:33:10,208
They go through all kinds of abuse

570
00:33:10,291 --> 00:33:12,750
and tell themselves
that everything's okay.

571
00:33:14,500 --> 00:33:15,375
[chuckles]

572
00:33:16,208 --> 00:33:17,708
That's me all over.

573
00:33:18,708 --> 00:33:20,666
<i>Maybe Manami was like that too.</i>

574
00:33:23,541 --> 00:33:25,666
- [door closes]
- [Karasuma] Hey, I'm back.

575
00:33:28,833 --> 00:33:30,833
[snoring]

576
00:33:35,541 --> 00:33:37,208
[Karasuma] You're kidding me.

577
00:33:38,875 --> 00:33:39,875
Okay, then.

578
00:33:43,625 --> 00:33:45,291
[snoring continues]

579
00:34:02,750 --> 00:34:04,000
[music fades]

580
00:34:05,416 --> 00:34:07,416
Thank you, Mr. Karasuma.

581
00:34:11,625 --> 00:34:12,958
[phone buzzes]

582
00:34:30,666 --> 00:34:32,833
Hello. Kujo speaking.

583
00:34:33,458 --> 00:34:36,333
[Kyogoku] <i>Attorney Kujo,</i>
<i>Koyama's been arrested.</i>

584
00:34:36,416 --> 00:34:37,875
<i>Please do something.</i>

585
00:34:42,291 --> 00:34:44,291
[closing theme song playing]

586
00:37:20,041 --> 00:37:21,416
[music fades]
